                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a postoperative client who has just returned from surgery for creation of a colostomy. The nurse inspects the colostomy stoma and recognizes that which is a normal assessment finding for this client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nNormal characteristics of a stoma include a rose to brick-red color indicating viable mucosa, mild to moderate edema during the initial postoperative period, and a small amount of oozing blood from the stoma mucosa (because of its high vascularity) when it is touched. A pale color may indicate anemia. A stoma that is dark red to purple indicates inadequate blood supply to the stoma or bowel due to adhesions, low blood flow state, or excessive tension on the bowel at the time of construction. A small amount of bleeding is considered normal, but a moderate to large amount of bleeding from the stoma mucosa could indicate coagulation factor deficiency, stomal varices secondary to portal hypertension, or lower gastrointestinal bleeding.",
                        "id": "7f02ba65ac4341fd8ec4809fa82404cc",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "4ada7c744b5c460a95258142713e30b5",
                                "content": "This is a normal, expected event."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9dcb1ca761fc40ad958b2285142bba68",
                                "content": "The client is experiencing early signs of ischemic bowel."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2a65cddda4884227be135a9f26409136",
                                "content": "The client should not have the nasogastric tube removed."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1218b9423c2b401a972656c1f84b820d",
                                "content": "This indicates inadequate preoperative bowel preparation."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "4ada7c744b5c460a95258142713e30b5",
                                    "content": "This is a normal, expected event."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
