                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client postoperatively after creation of a colostomy to treat a bowel tumor. What is an appropriate potential client problem?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAltered body image for a client who is postoperative after creation of a colostomy relates to loss of bowel control, the presence of a stoma, the release of fecal material onto the abdomen, the passage of flatus, odor, and the need for an appliance (external pouch). There are no data in the question to support sexual dysfunction or fear. Inadequate nutritional intake rather than excessive intake would more likely be a client problem.\n",
                        "id": "c4775ecb179a4b78a51604d5bc9058ef",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "0b472e51f66b4200995c59649710683e",
                                "content": "Use 500 to 1000 mL of warm tap water."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "84f08f528f2742638ae7c595d28d8e95",
                                "content": "Suspend the irrigant 36 inches above the stoma."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f708f89966cb4623ae38b8559280be76",
                                "content": "Insert the irrigation cone ½ inch into the stoma."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9abe85ad166b42e9ade350c700adee29",
                                "content": "If cramping occurs, open the irrigation clamp farther."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "0b472e51f66b4200995c59649710683e",
                                    "content": "Use 500 to 1000 mL of warm tap water."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "84f08f528f2742638ae7c595d28d8e95",
                                    "content": "Suspend the irrigant 36 inches above the stoma."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "f708f89966cb4623ae38b8559280be76",
                                    "content": "Insert the irrigation cone ½ inch into the stoma."
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "9abe85ad166b42e9ade350c700adee29",
                                    "content": "If cramping occurs, open the irrigation clamp farther."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
